She has now lost half of her month's pay after her bosses discovered her web activities, according to The Local.

The insurance agency ruled she had been 'disloyal to the employer' by being 'inactive' instead of helping customers during both paid overtime and scheduled work over the summer

The woman is just one of several Försäkringskassan employees to have faced disciplinary action for browsing the internet while at work. 

In another case, an employee spent around 50 hours during just one month visiting 350 websites when she was supposed to be working.

