It is not the first time an employee has been fired after being caught using Facebook in the workplace.

Last year, a DVLA worker was sacked after accessing the social networking site while working - even though there was no suggestion he had criticised his employers on there.

The agency was labelled 'draconian' by online critics following the dismissal, which was disclosed under the Freedom of Information Act.

